        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 11 at 1:03PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 102 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 7 miles northwest of Spartanburg to 4 miles
east of Greenville Downtown. Movement was southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Reidville, Wellford, Roebuck, Lyman, Spartanburg, GSP Airport, Moore,
USC Upstate, Five Forks, and Greer.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
